Text.Value: There are... but you need to finish what you came here for. If half of the rumours about what was done to you are true... well, I won't stand in your way.
There are... but with the Mother Superior gone, I don't know if I can stay here to reminisce. Perhaps there's another enclave out there for me.
I am under no illusions about the nature of our creed. But to find a home, to find acceptance for who I am... that is no small thing.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little tough. 'you don't need to explain the sky's blue'

Text.Value: But I can imagine that is hard to believe. Give me a day, and I'll leave here. You'll never be troubled by me again.
*You recall the memory you recovered by eating the noblestalk - part of you understands that this is the same person you saw, but different, and with a new name.*
Still, we need to be careful... The Mother Superior holds a tight grip on this place. But perhaps I can help you in the meanwhile.
Of course. I am just a quartermaster - I would have been little use to you in battle.
Nocturne? Can't say I know you. Interesting name, though.
Come see me when you have time - I work as quartermaster now. I can sell you some things... and we can catch up.
Perhaps she was telling you what you wanted to hear. To keep you in Lady Shar's embrace.
Remind me.
I'm glad to see you're all right, even if you don't remember me.
Perhaps she was telling you what you wanted to hear. To keep you bound to Shar.
There are... but you need to finish what you came here for. Everyone knows you've been blessed, that you're coming for the Mother Superior. I won't stand in your way.
It seems the whispers were right on that last part, my lady. At some point she confused her ambitions for the Nightsinger's will.
Not that new. You inspired me to do it, actually.
She is gone, but the Dark Lady is always with me. Perhaps there's another enclave out there for me.
I must give the Mother Superior due credit, though. She accepted it with a nod. 'The Dark Lady guides us all,' she said. 'We find our true selves in her embrace.'
I serve as quartermaster - see me whenever you seek supplies. And perhaps we could catch up... If you wish, of course.
It's possible - don't think I haven't considered it. But to find a home, to find acceptance for who I am... that is no small thing.
Not as glad as I am.
I'm glad you're happy.
Most, but not me. You may not remember, but we shared a lot together once. Good times, hard times... I will not turn on you. Even if it angers Lady Shar.
Most would consider us enemies, not friends.
If you wish it of me... of course. I work as the quartermaster. Come see me whenever you wish.
Very supportive of her.
It seems the whispers were right, on that last part. At some point she confused her ambitions for the Nightsinger's will.
I'll leave come tomorrow. Come see me before then - I was working as quartermaster. I can sell you some things to aid you... and we can catch up.
But no matter - you rule us now. What comes next?
But now it seems you've turned on both the Mother Superior and Lady Shar...
What comes next? My rule over this place. You will resume your duties.
Most would consider us enemies, not friends.
I remember the other initiates used to tease you about your name - the one you chose to honour Lady Shar. But I never found it funny...
Shar is evil. She ruins lives. The acceptance of her disciple is nothing worth cherishing.
We... we trained together. We used to be close.
Most would consider us enemies, not friends.
But enough of that - I can't believe you're back.
*This seems to be the person from the memory recovered by eating the noblestalk - but changed, and with a different name.*
Still, we need to be careful... The Mother Superior holds a tight grip on this place. But perhaps I can help you in the meanwhile.
You may be free of the Dark Lady, but not everyone is as brave. I'm afraid.
I keep forgetting how little you must remember - you inspired the name, actually.
They... they whispered it was a suicide mission, this search for the artefact you were sent on. Some even thought it was the Mother Superior's plan alone, and not what Lady Shar wanted...
Do I detect a trace of scepticism? I know it might be hard to believe, but you can find acceptance in the unlikeliest of places.
Come see me before then, if you wish. I was working as quartermaster. I can sell you some things to aid you... and we can catch up.
I do not wish to argue the point. I'm too glad to see you for that.
I... I remember you. But you're different. Very different. And that name is new.
If we were - are - friends, there must be all sorts of things you could tell me.
Come see me when you have time - I work as quartermaster now. I can sell you some things... and we can catch up.
What comes next? The Chamber of Loss. Viconia is gone, and soon I will rule.
Remind me.
But at least my wares can still aid you. Come to me whenever you need supplies... and perhaps we can catch up as well.
Viconia's gone, and this place can rot as far as I'm concerned. You should leave.
How did they react?
I did not see you amongst my supporters when I faced Viconia - can I trust you?
Be careful... Whatever she has planned, I don't think she'll shed any tears if you were a casualty along the way.
They were attacking who you were. I never found it funny, but wasn't quite sure why. Eventually I realised it was because I wasn't happy with who I was.
Shadowheart... I wasn't sure if I'd ever lay eyes on you again. It's me, Nocturne. Do you remember?
Every way you can imagine. Scorn, indifference, acceptance, confusion. Some tried to taunt me, attack me... but luckily I learned a few tricks from you about how to handle them.
I'm glad you're happy.
Then you are more than a friend - you are soon to be my leader, my lady.
I remember none of this - or at least, almost none of it.
I... I remember you. But you're different. Very different. And that name is new.
Of course, my lady.
I couldn't keep going like that. But seeing how you fought on, I realised that I didn't have to. From then on, I was Nocturne. It wasn't easy... but everything started to make sense. I could breathe.
Perhaps I can aid you all the same - it seems the Dark Lady holds you in high favour.
I understand. Allow me to remember for the both of us - it changed my life for the better.

Synopsis: Shadowheart meets with her old friend once again. Talking about the past and discussing what the future is going to look like. Nocturne is a MtF transgender character, which Shadowheart may realise after piecing together information from a fragmented memory she recalled before.
